608
00:54:42,406 --> 00:54:44,074
I didn't say anything.

609
00:54:44,158 --> 00:54:47,453
- You said "do something."
- No, I didn't. I wasn't talking to anybody.

610
00:54:47,536 --> 00:54:50,914
- Talk to me!
- I don't know anything. Please stop.

611
00:54:50,998 --> 00:54:52,583
Stay where you are.

612
00:54:53,750 --> 00:54:55,252
Truman?

613
00:54:56,670 --> 00:54:57,963
Truman.

614
00:54:58,589 --> 00:55:02,259
Oh, thank God!

615
00:55:05,387 --> 00:55:10,184
How can anyone expect me to carry on
under these conditions?

616
00:55:10,476 --> 00:55:12,478
It's unprofessional.

617
00:55:13,395 --> 00:55:14,730
It's okay.

618
00:55:17,608 --> 00:55:21,862
Everything's going to be okay.
It's all gonna be fine.

619
00:55:25,407 --> 00:55:27,576
I don't know what to think, Marlon.

620
00:55:31,705 --> 00:55:33,916
Maybe I'm losing my mind, but...

621
00:55:38,253 --> 00:55:41,590
It feels like the whole world
revolves around me somehow.

622
00:55:44,009 --> 00:55:46,678
That's a lot of world for one man,
Truman.

623
00:55:48,847 --> 00:55:50,933
Sure that's not wishful thinking?

624
00:55:51,350 --> 00:55:54,394
You wishing you'd made something
more out of yourself?

625
00:55:55,270 --> 00:55:57,439
Come on, who hasn't sat in the john,

626
