639
00:56:43,277 --> 00:56:44,653
You remember that?

640
00:56:45,529 --> 00:56:47,990
You were out of school for
about a month.

641
00:56:54,371 --> 00:56:57,165
You're the closest thing I ever had
to a brother, Truman.

642
00:57:03,672 --> 00:57:05,299
I know that things

643
00:57:06,466 --> 00:57:10,554
haven't really worked out for either of us
like we used to dream they would.

644
00:57:11,513 --> 00:57:15,350
I know that feeling, when it's like
everything's slipping away

645
00:57:16,602 --> 00:57:18,729
and you don't want to believe it,

646
00:57:19,354 --> 00:57:22,065
so you look for answers
somewhere else, but...

647
00:57:28,572 --> 00:57:30,073
The point is,

648
00:57:30,782 --> 00:57:33,410
I'd gladly walk in front of traffic for you.

649
00:57:39,458 --> 00:57:43,253
<i>The point is, I would gladly
step in front of traffic for you, Truman.</i>

650
00:57:44,421 --> 00:57:47,674
And the last thing I'd ever do
is lie to you.

